{
  "uuid": "7593c62fb68020b9f3b4462a0e8d3dc2",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cloud Engineer Lead",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><strong>Cloud Onboarding & Adoption</strong></p><ul><li>Lead business and technical consultations to support tenant onboarding to cloud platforms.</li><li>Resolve onboarding challenges in collaboration with internal and external stakeholders.</li><li>Recommend technical solutions and propose process enhancements for smoother adoption.</li><li>Develop and deliver onboarding materials, service documentation, and workflows.</li></ul><p><strong>Project & Performance Reporting</strong></p><ul><li>Track and report onboarding progress, KPIs, and resource forecasts.</li><li>Maintain dashboards and trackers for project and management reporting.</li></ul><p><strong>Stakeholder Engagement & Knowledge Management</strong></p><ul><li>Advise teams on cloud offerings, standards, processes, and best practices.</li><li>Maintain up-to-date knowledge resources and collaborate on training initiatives.</li><li>Drive change management activities and communication efforts (e.g., townhalls, briefings).</li></ul><p><strong>Continuous Improvement</strong></p><ul><li>Enhance onboarding workflows and reduce timelines for improved user satisfaction.</li><li>Collect feedback to refine policies, processes, and cloud capabilities.</li><li>Support implementation of emerging cloud technologies and training programs.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in IT, Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Minimum 4 years of experience in IT, with hands-on cloud exposure.</li><li>Professional-level certification in AWS, Azure, GCP, Oracle, VMware, or Nutanix.</li><li>Experience in full Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) projects.</li><li>Strong knowledge of cloud infrastructure and services.</li><li>Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and organizational skills.</li><li>Proficiency in MS Office and project management tools (e.g., MS Project, JIRA).</li></ul><p><strong>Work Location:</strong> North</p><p><br /></p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p>Please email a copy of your detailed resume to<strong> bianca@talentsis.com.sg </strong>for immediate processing.</p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312).</p>",
